# Marky Implementation Roadmap

## Project Structure
- Trainers (AST & Semantic)
  - AST Markov Trainer
    - Extract AST sequences
    - Build n-gram models
    - Export to Python
  - Semantic Pattern Extractor
    - Define CodePattern enum
    - Detect 50+ patterns
    - Classify constructs
  - Semantic Markov Trainer
    - Use pattern analyzer
    - Build semantic transitions
    - Export models

- Core Interfaces
  - Data Types
    - NextNodeSuggestion
    - NextPatternSuggestion
    - ASTContext
    - ValidationResult
  - Model Loading
    - Standard interfaces
    - Version compatibility

- Agent Integration Layer
  - AST Code Guide
    - Fast lookups
    - Temperature sampling
    - Logit biasing
    - Fallback mechanisms
  - Semantic Code Guide
    - Pattern templates
    - Prompt enhancement
    - Pattern chains
    - Intent detection
  - Performance Optimization
    - Caching layer
    - Pre-warmed cache
    - Benchmarking

- Advanced Features
  - REST API Service
    - /ast/suggest
    - /semantic/suggest
    - /health endpoints
  - Prompt Engineering
    - AST enhancement
    - Semantic enhancement
    - Guidance generation
  - Reference Agent
    - Semantic coding agent
    - Iterative refinement
    - Pattern-driven generation

- CLI & Tools
  - Training Commands
    - marky train --type ast
    - marky train --type semantic
  - Analysis Tools
    - Pattern analysis
    - Statistics printing
    - Benchmarking
  - Full Test Suite
    - Unit tests
    - Integration tests
    - Performance tests

## Implementation Phases
- Phase 1: Foundation (Trainers)
  - 1.1: ASTMarkovTrainer ✓
  - 1.2: SemanticPatternExtractor ✓
  - 1.3: SemanticMarkovTrainer ✓
  - 1.4: Model Types ✓
  
- Phase 2: Agent Integration
  - 2.1: ASTCodeGuide ✓
  - 2.2: SemanticCodeGuide ✓
  - 2.3: Performance ✓
  
- Phase 3: Advanced
  - 3.1: REST API ✓
  - 3.2: Prompt Enhancement ✓
  - 3.3: Semantic Agent ✓
  
- Phase 4: Polish
  - 4.1: CLI Tools ✓
  - 4.2: Tests ✓
  - 4.3: Documentation ✓

## Code Pattern Taxonomy (~50 patterns)
- Control Flow (5)
  - IF_NONE_CHECK
  - IF_NOT_NONE
  - IF_EMPTY_CHECK
  - IF_TYPE_CHECK
  - GUARD_CLAUSE
  
- Loop Patterns (6)
  - LOOP_ACCUMULATE
  - LOOP_TRANSFORM
  - LOOP_FILTER
  - LOOP_ENUMERATE
  - LOOP_ZIP
  - LOOP_DICT_ITEMS
  
- Return Patterns (5)
  - RETURN_NONE
  - RETURN_BOOL
  - RETURN_LIST
  - RETURN_DICT
  - RETURN_COMPUTED
  
- Data Structures (8)
  - INIT_EMPTY_LIST
  - INIT_EMPTY_DICT
  - INIT_COUNTER
  - APPEND_TO_LIST
  - DICT_UPDATE
  - DICT_GET_DEFAULT
  - DEFAULT_DICT_PATTERN
  - UNPACKING
  
- Error Handling (5)
  - TRY_EXCEPT_PASS
  - TRY_EXCEPT_LOG
  - TRY_EXCEPT_RERAISE
  - TRY_FINALLY
  - CONTEXT_MANAGER
  
- Functions & Classes (6)
  - FUNCTION_VALIDATOR
  - FUNCTION_TRANSFORMER
  - INIT_METHOD
  - PROPERTY_GETTER
  - CLASS_METHOD
  - STATIC_METHOD
  
- Comprehensions (3)
  - LIST_COMPREHENSION
  - DICT_COMPREHENSION
  - GENERATOR_EXPRESSION
  
- API Patterns (3)
  - API_VALIDATION
  - API_ERROR_RESPONSE
  - API_SUCCESS_RESPONSE
  
- Other Idioms (8)
  - TERNARY_EXPRESSION
  - STRING_FORMAT
  - LOGGING_CALL
  - EARLY_RETURN_SUCCESS
  - EARLY_RETURN_FAILURE
  - PROPERTY_SETTER
  - FUNCTION_DECORATOR
  - FUNCTION_FACTORY

## Key Metrics
- AST Trainer
  - Vocabulary: ~200 node types
  - Training speed: 1000 files/min
  - Model size: 10-50MB
  
- Semantic Trainer
  - Vocabulary: ~50 patterns
  - Training speed: 500 files/min
  - Model size: 1-10MB
  - 5-10x faster inference
  
- Performance Targets
  - Lookup latency: <1ms (cached)
  - Throughput: 50K queries/sec
  - Cache hit rate: >90% (warmed)

## Test Coverage Requirements
- Phase 1: >90% coverage
  - Unit tests per module
  - Pattern detection tests
  - Model export validation
  
- Phase 2: >85% coverage
  - Guide interface tests
  - Fallback mechanism tests
  - Cache performance tests
  
- Phase 3: >80% coverage
  - API endpoint tests
  - Agent integration tests
  - End-to-end tests
  
- Phase 4: >95% coverage
  - Full test suite
  - CLI validation
  - Documentation examples

## Success Criteria Per Phase
- Phase 1
  - Parse 1000+ files successfully
  - Extract 40+ pattern types
  - Export valid, executable models
  - Unit tests pass
  
- Phase 2
  - <1ms lookup latency
  - >90% fallback success
  - 50%+ performance improvement with cache
  - All agent scenarios validated
  
- Phase 3
  - 1000 req/sec API throughput
  - Improved generation quality
  - 95%+ valid code generation
  - <5 seconds per function
  
- Phase 4
  - Intuitive CLI interface
  - >95% test coverage
  - Complete documentation
  - Production-ready

## Dependencies
- External
  - Python 3.8+
  - ast (stdlib)
  - collections (stdlib)
  - numpy (optional, for logit biasing)
  - Flask (optional, for REST API)
  
- Internal
  - Phase 1 required for all later phases
  - Phase 2 required for Phase 3
  - Phase 3 builds on Phase 2

## Known Challenges
- Pattern detection accuracy
  - Mitigated: More training data, better heuristics
  
- Memory for large models
  - Mitigated: Quantization, sparse storage
  
- Edge cases in incomplete code
  - Mitigated: Multiple fallback strategies
  
- Sparse state space coverage
  - Mitigated: Aggregation fallbacks, defaults
